name: Paul Golia
notes: Name entered into SUR issue (for PEN club meeting in 1937 in Buenos Aires) as "Paul Golia". There is a "Pavel Golia" (information used to fill out this entry) that matches his information (especially the fact that both individuals were writers and associated with Ljubljana). There is a strong change that the SUR issue incorrectly wrote his name as "Paul" instead of "Pavel."

name: Rabindranath Tagore
notes: Fell ill during a trip to Lima, Perú (flu) and had to cancel his trip there and instead stay in Buenos Aires, Argentina (where his ship docked); when Victoria heard of this, she rushed to the hotel where he was staying and put him up in one of her homes. This happened in November of 1924, and he stayed with her until January 1925. They met again in Paris, France in June of 1930
